VHyderabad N. Subbalaxhmi presented an enchanting vocal concert under the auspices of Sri Rama Gana Sabha Trust at the Bala Kala Vidhanam Hall in Renga Nagar, Tiruchi, recently.Subbalaxhmi commenced her programme with the &#8216;Ninnebhajana' kirtana composed by Tyagaraja in Gambhiranattai. Later she rendered &#8216;Renganathude' the Ponnaiyya Pillai kriti in raga Sourashtram followed by &#8216;Manasuloni' by Tyagaraja in Hindolam and &#8216;Kathanakuthuhala Priye' compiled by Seshayyar in Kathanakuthuhalam.Lauded by the rasikasThe highlight of the programme was her &#8216;Marivere' by Patnam Subramania Iyer in raga Shanmukhapriya. Shertalai M.N. Sathyamoorthy's elaboration on the violin was effortless which earned him applause from the rasikas.Another highlight was &#8216;Palinchu Kamakshi' by Syama Sastri in Madhyamavathi. This song brought to light the ebullience of Subbalaxhmi. At the end of the song Tiruchi B. Swaminathan and Malaikottai R.M. Deenadayalu rendered tani avartanam in mridangam and morsing respectively.Subbalaxhmi continued with &#8216;Marukelara' by Tyagaraja in Jayantasri and wound up her concert with Papanasam Sivan's &#8216;Srinivasa' in Hamsanandi.
